# .cursorrules — RMP x OSU Chrome Extension

## Project Overview
A Chrome Extension (Manifest V3) that injects RateMyProfessors ratings inline
on the Ohio State University course search page (classes.osu.edu).
Personal use only — never to be published to the Chrome Web Store.

---

## Hard Rules — Never Violate These

### No build tooling
- NO npm, NO package.json, NO webpack, NO babel, NO bundler of any kind
- NO external libraries or CDN imports
- Pure vanilla JavaScript ES modules only
- The extension is loaded via chrome://extensions → Load Unpacked — that's it

### No CORS violations
- ALL fetch calls to ratemyprofessors.com MUST go through src/background/index.js only
- Content scripts NEVER make direct fetch calls to external domains
- Content scripts communicate with background ONLY via chrome.runtime.sendMessage / onMessage
- Violating this will silently fail due to CORS and is a hard architectural error

### Manifest V3 only
- Use "service_worker" in background, NOT "scripts" (that's MV2)
- Use chrome.storage.local, NOT localStorage
- No eval(), no remote code execution
- host_permissions must include both "https://classes.osu.edu/*" and "https://www.ratemyprofessors.com/*"

### File responsibilities — never cross these boundaries
- background/index.js → ONLY: receive messages, call RMP API, return data
- content/scraper.js → ONLY: find instructor name DOM nodes, return them
- content/injector.js → ONLY: create and insert badge HTML elements into DOM
- content/tooltip.js → ONLY: show/hide/position the hover tooltip
- content/index.js → ONLY: boot the MutationObserver, wire the other modules together
- shared/constants.js → ONLY: hardcoded values (no logic)
- shared/utils.js → ONLY: pure functions with no DOM or Chrome API access

---

## Code Style Rules

- Every function must have a JSDoc comment (description + @param + @return)
- Functions must be under 30 lines — break them up if longer
- No inline styles anywhere — all styles live in src/styles/badge.css
- Use const by default, let only when reassignment is genuinely needed, never var
- Prefer early returns over nested if/else
- Name booleans with is/has prefix: isEnabled, hasRating
- Cache DOM queries — never query the same selector twice in a loop
- Always handle the case where an API call returns null/undefined gracefully
- No console.log left in final code — use a single DEBUG constant in constants.js

---

## RMP API Rules

- The OSU school ID on RateMyProfessors is hardcoded in constants.js — never hardcode it elsewhere
- Always strip middle names before sending to RMP search (OSU uses full legal names)
- Always verify the returned professor's school matches Ohio State before injecting rating
- If numRatings < 3, show the rating but add a "few ratings" warning in the tooltip
- If wouldTakeAgainPercent === -1, display as "N/A" not a number
- Cache results in a Map keyed by normalized name for the session to avoid duplicate API calls

---

## DOM / OSU Page Rules

- Use MutationObserver in content/index.js — the OSU page loads results via XHR, not full page loads
- Before processing a name node, check if it already has a badge injected (data-rmp-injected attribute)
  to prevent duplicate badges on re-renders
- "TBA" instructor names must be skipped — check in scraper.js before returning
- Debounce the MutationObserver callback (300ms) to avoid thrashing on rapid DOM updates
- All selectors are defined in constants.js — never hardcode a selector string in content scripts

---

## What To Do When Stuck

- If the OSU DOM selector stops working: open DevTools on classes.osu.edu,
  find the instructor name element, update INSTRUCTOR_NAME_SELECTOR in constants.js
- If the RMP API returns 401/403: the Bearer token in constants.js may have changed.
  Open DevTools on ratemyprofessors.com, go to Network tab, filter by "graphql",
  search for any professor, copy the Authorization header value, update RMP_AUTH_TOKEN
- If MutationObserver fires too often: increase OBSERVER_DEBOUNCE_MS in constants.js
